1
00:00:01,718 --> 00:00:03,095
Parfait, parfait!

2
00:00:03,555 --> 00:00:07,103
I'm absolutely sure it's going to be
the Tropical Strawberry Parfait!

3
00:00:07,521 --> 00:00:09,734
No way, I've got a feeling today's gonna be

4
00:00:09,817 --> 00:00:12,323
that gorgeous strawberry chiffon cake!

5
00:00:15,370 --> 00:00:18,083
And now, the announcement.

6
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:21,507
The winner of tonight's strawberry battle is...

7
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:26,684
The one who made the Tropical Strawberry Parfait,

8
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:29,690
Patissier Shuhei Kurimura!

9
00:00:29,774 --> 00:00:32,988
(Crowd cheers) He successfully defends his title as champion!

10
00:00:33,072 --> 00:00:34,909
Wow! Oh man...

11
00:00:34,992 --> 00:00:38,082
I really thought the champion was gonna lose today.

12
00:00:38,165 --> 00:00:42,383
It's amazing. That's six weeks in a row now!

13
00:00:42,758 --> 00:00:44,345
We'll see you again next week

14
00:00:44,428 --> 00:00:47,267
on "Which Sweet Will Show"!

15
00:00:47,977 --> 00:00:49,020
Phew...

16
00:00:50,190 --> 00:00:53,571
Hey, delinquent girl.

17
00:00:53,655 --> 00:00:56,995
Don't you have to go home? It's almost 8 o'clock.

18
00:00:57,078 --> 00:00:58,373
Tch.

19
00:00:58,456 --> 00:01:02,214
I'm just scoping it out. I'm coming as an audience member

20
00:01:02,297 --> 00:01:04,218
with Ran next week.

21
00:01:04,552 --> 00:01:05,554
Hmph.

22
00:01:05,637 --> 00:01:10,439
Oh, right. My dad's got connections. You wanna come too, Uncle?

23
00:01:10,522 --> 00:01:13,987
Who'd want to go to some saccharine, lazy excuse for a food show...

24
00:01:14,070 --> 00:01:17,286
Oh? Too bad. I heard Yoko Okino's gonna be

25
00:01:17,369 --> 00:01:20,500
a guest judge.

26
00:01:21,878 --> 00:01:25,343
I'll be going, Lady Sonoko!

27
00:01:25,427 --> 00:01:26,512
Heheheh.

28
00:01:26,971 --> 00:01:29,268
This old man's so easy...

29
00:01:29,602 --> 00:01:32,316
So then, would you be so kind as to escort us

30
00:01:32,399 --> 00:01:34,278
in your rental car that day, Uncle?

31
00:01:34,361 --> 00:01:36,783
Hmph. As you wish.

32
00:01:36,866 --> 00:01:40,457
Heheheh. But what about the other person?

33
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:43,171
We've got invitations for five people.

34
00:01:43,254 --> 00:01:46,803
And my mom said she has to work...

35
00:01:46,886 --> 00:01:48,013
Oh, then how about...

36
00:01:48,097 --> 00:01:49,183
Hmm?

37
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:55,612
♪~♪

38
00:02:02,584 --> 00:02:06,133
The black of shadow, the depth of darkness—
the light of deduction tears right through them.

39
00:02:06,217 --> 00:02:10,267
An impossible crime during the recording.
The mystery hidden inside the fruit box.

40
00:02:10,350 --> 00:02:12,145
He sees through the one and only truth.

41
00:02:12,229 --> 00:02:14,107
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

42
00:02:14,191 --> 00:02:16,529
His name is Detective Conan!

43
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:46,522
♪~♪

44
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:54,128
"A Treasure Box Full of Fruits (Part 1)"

45
00:03:54,128 --> 00:03:57,042
Huh? You mean I can go too?

46
00:03:57,125 --> 00:03:59,548
Yeah, Conan-kun insisted.

47
00:03:59,631 --> 00:04:01,843
Is... is that so?

48
00:04:01,927 --> 00:04:03,430
Uh... yeah.

49
00:04:03,514 --> 00:04:06,728
Well, if you're inviting me, I can't say no.

50
00:04:08,428 --> 00:04:11,728
There's something I wanna ask her anyway.

51
00:04:13,328 --> 00:04:15,728
Well, we just have to make sure we don't stand out too much

52
00:04:15,728 --> 00:04:17,028
and catch the eye of the judge,

53
00:04:17,028 --> 00:04:19,128
Mr. Takegi.

54
00:04:19,128 --> 00:04:20,428
Mr. Takegi?

55
00:04:20,428 --> 00:04:22,328
You don't know him?

56
00:04:22,328 --> 00:04:25,228
He's a giant in Japan's patisserie world.

57
00:04:25,228 --> 00:04:28,728
The Legend of Sweets, Shoutoku Takegi.

58
00:04:28,728 --> 00:04:31,728
So what happens if he does notice you?

59
00:04:31,728 --> 00:04:33,128
In the middle of the show,

60
00:04:33,128 --> 00:04:36,428
Mr. Takegi picks someone from the audience

61
00:04:36,428 --> 00:04:40,728
to do a taste test.

62
00:04:40,728 --> 00:04:43,428
If you guess the fruit used correctly,

63
00:04:43,428 --> 00:04:44,528
you get to eat the winning sweets

64
00:04:44,528 --> 00:04:47,528
from that round.

65
00:04:47,528 --> 00:04:49,128
But if you get it wrong,

66
00:04:49,128 --> 00:04:51,728
they kick you out of the studio immediately.

67
00:04:51,728 --> 00:04:54,728
Is this Takegi guy really that strict?

68
00:04:54,728 --> 00:04:56,628
Yeah. I mean, the current champion's been winning

69
00:04:56,628 --> 00:04:59,028
for six weeks straight,

70
00:04:59,028 --> 00:05:01,928
but Mr. Takegi's scores are always harsh.

71
00:05:01,928 --> 00:05:05,628
Well, the challenger's scores are even lower.

72
00:05:06,728 --> 00:05:08,228
Oh, come to think of it,

73
00:05:08,228 --> 00:05:10,728
I heard that champion Kurimura's shop

74
00:05:10,728 --> 00:05:13,028
is opening another branch.

75
00:05:13,028 --> 00:05:16,928
I wish he'd open one in Beika Town too.

76
00:05:16,928 --> 00:05:18,228
But don't you think

77
00:05:18,228 --> 00:05:20,928
that champion's kind of suspicious?

78
00:05:20,928 --> 00:05:23,328
I mean, yesterday he just happened

79
00:05:23,328 --> 00:05:25,428
to bring ice cream and jelly that go with strawberries,

80
00:05:25,428 --> 00:05:26,928
the theme fruit.

81
00:05:26,928 --> 00:05:29,128
What are you saying?

82
00:05:29,128 --> 00:05:32,228
That the champion's cheating?

83
00:05:32,228 --> 00:05:34,428
I don't think that's it.

84
00:05:34,428 --> 00:05:36,428
Even the TV staff don't know

85
00:05:36,428 --> 00:05:38,628
what the theme fruit is until the box is opened.

86
00:05:38,628 --> 00:05:41,428
The box is that old-fashioned iron box

87
00:05:41,428 --> 00:05:43,828
they open at the start of the show, right?

88
00:05:43,828 --> 00:05:45,728
Any TV staffer could just

89
00:05:45,728 --> 00:05:48,028
sneak a peek, no?

90
00:05:48,028 --> 00:05:51,028
That's the thing—they made it so you can't.

91
00:05:51,028 --> 00:05:54,228
Each time, this fruit selection expert

92
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:57,728
packs the box full of the theme fruit.

93
00:05:57,728 --> 00:05:58,728
After packing it,

94
00:05:58,728 --> 00:06:01,528
they lock the box and send it to the TV station.

95
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:03,428
The producer who receives it

96
00:06:03,428 --> 00:06:05,628
puts a different lock on it

97
00:06:05,628 --> 00:06:08,028
and sends it back to the expert.

98
00:06:08,028 --> 00:06:10,328
The expert opens his own lock,

99
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:13,528
sends it back to the TV station again,

100
00:06:13,528 --> 00:06:17,028
and at the start of the show,

101
00:06:17,028 --> 00:06:18,328
the MC, who gets the key from the producer,

102
00:06:18,328 --> 00:06:22,528
opens the box.

103
00:06:22,528 --> 00:06:24,228
That's the first time anyone finds out

104
00:06:24,228 --> 00:06:25,828
what the theme fruit is.

105
00:06:25,828 --> 00:06:27,628
I see.

106
00:06:27,628 --> 00:06:29,328
It's an old code.

107
00:06:29,328 --> 00:06:31,328
A code?

108
00:06:31,328 --> 00:06:32,328
Back when communication devices

109
00:06:32,328 --> 00:06:35,028
weren't as advanced,

110
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:38,528
that's how people exchanged secret documents.

111
00:06:38,528 --> 00:06:39,728
With this method,

112
00:06:39,728 --> 00:06:41,628
only the people with the keys

113
00:06:41,628 --> 00:06:43,428
can see the contents.

114
00:06:43,428 --> 00:06:44,728
Oh, right!

115
00:06:44,728 --> 00:06:46,828
So even the people transporting it

116
00:06:46,828 --> 00:06:48,228
can't sneak a peek

117
00:06:48,228 --> 00:06:50,128
even if they wanted to.

118
00:06:50,128 --> 00:06:52,728
So how do we avoid standing out?

119
00:06:52,728 --> 00:06:54,528
How do we not get noticed?

120
00:06:54,528 --> 00:06:57,328
There are a lot of women in the audience...

121
00:06:57,328 --> 00:07:00,928
Why don't you try wearing something more girly?

122
00:07:00,928 --> 00:07:03,228
Girly?

123
00:07:03,228 --> 00:07:05,128
Well, the one who'll stand out the most

124
00:07:05,128 --> 00:07:07,328
is that mustached old man anyway.

125
00:07:09,828 --> 00:07:11,728
Oh, Mr. Takegi.

126
00:07:11,728 --> 00:07:13,828
If you're asking about the fruit for tomorrow's show,

127
00:07:13,828 --> 00:07:16,028
I've already finished packing them.

128
00:07:16,028 --> 00:07:17,128
Oh?

129
00:07:17,128 --> 00:07:18,628
We've brought in choice fruit

130
00:07:18,628 --> 00:07:21,428
from all over the country again this time,

131
00:07:21,428 --> 00:07:23,028
so rest assured.

132
00:07:23,028 --> 00:07:26,128
Well then, let me confirm.

133
00:07:26,128 --> 00:07:27,328
Ah, no.

134
00:07:27,328 --> 00:07:28,628
Even you, Mr. Takegi,

135
00:07:28,628 --> 00:07:30,528
can't see the contents.

136
00:07:30,528 --> 00:07:33,328
That's what we agreed, isn't it?

137
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:34,928
Don't worry.

138
00:07:34,928 --> 00:07:37,628
It's not the contents I want to see.

139
00:07:37,628 --> 00:07:41,028
It's the key.

140
00:07:45,128 --> 00:07:47,928
Hmm... seems it's properly locked.

141
00:07:47,928 --> 00:07:49,328
Of course.

142
00:07:49,328 --> 00:07:53,328
I trust no one saw you packing the fruit?

143
00:07:53,328 --> 00:07:56,628
Yes. As always, I packed it alone

144
00:07:56,628 --> 00:07:59,028
in this storeroom.

145
00:07:59,028 --> 00:08:00,828
As camouflage, I also brought in

146
00:08:00,828 --> 00:08:05,228
fruit boxes meant for restaurants and other businesses,

147
00:08:05,228 --> 00:08:08,628
so even the delivery services had no idea.

148
00:08:08,628 --> 00:08:10,928
If that's the case,

149
00:08:10,928 --> 00:08:14,928
it could only leak from your mouth.

150
00:08:16,428 --> 00:08:19,028
Oh, has the forbidden fruit box arrived?

151
00:08:19,028 --> 00:08:20,428
Then hurry up and lock it

152
00:08:20,428 --> 00:08:22,028
and send it back, Furuya-chan.

153
00:08:22,028 --> 00:08:23,828
Oh, right.

154
00:08:23,828 --> 00:08:25,228
Yes sir.

155
00:08:25,228 --> 00:08:27,428
The padlock is in my desk as usual.

156
00:08:27,428 --> 00:08:29,528
No matter what,

157
00:08:29,528 --> 00:08:31,428
don't you dare try to peek inside.

158
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,328
Okay?

159
00:08:33,328 --> 00:08:34,728
Mr. Takegi just gave me an earful

160
00:08:34,728 --> 00:08:38,228
before the last recording.

161
00:08:38,228 --> 00:08:39,928
No can do.

162
00:08:39,928 --> 00:08:43,028
It's already locked with another key.

163
00:08:43,028 --> 00:08:45,528
Oh, right.

164
00:08:45,528 --> 00:08:47,928
They're still doing that tedious method?

165
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:50,028
Then why doesn't Takegi just pack the fruit himself

166
00:08:50,028 --> 00:08:51,628
and lock it?

167
00:08:51,628 --> 00:08:53,328
He says he wants to be surprised too,

168
00:08:53,328 --> 00:08:56,528
seeing the ingredients during the show.

169
00:08:56,528 --> 00:08:59,228
Well, he's getting old.

170
00:08:59,228 --> 00:09:00,328
Actually,

171
00:09:00,328 --> 00:09:04,028
we've already got someone lined up to replace him.

172
00:09:09,728 --> 00:09:10,828
How about it?

173
00:09:17,028 --> 00:09:19,528
I look a bit more girlish, don't I?

174
00:09:20,528 --> 00:09:21,728
Um...

175
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:24,228
What part of you is different from usual?

176
00:09:26,028 --> 00:09:29,328
I'm wearing cute flower-patterned underwear.

177
00:09:29,328 --> 00:09:31,328
It was a little embarrassing, though.

178
00:09:33,728 --> 00:09:36,528
What's the point if no one can see it?

179
00:09:36,528 --> 00:09:39,028
Anyway, where's Yoko? She's not here.

180
00:09:39,028 --> 00:09:40,728
If she's a judge,

181
00:09:40,728 --> 00:09:42,028
isn't she waiting in another room

182
00:09:42,028 --> 00:09:44,028
for the sweets to be brought in?

183
00:09:44,028 --> 00:09:45,428
Huh?

184
00:09:45,428 --> 00:09:46,428
Don't worry,

185
00:09:46,428 --> 00:09:47,828
she'll be on that monitor.

186
00:09:47,828 --> 00:09:49,828
Then it's no different from watching TV at home!

187
00:09:51,228 --> 00:09:55,328
Um...

188
00:09:55,328 --> 00:09:57,328
Ah, sorry. We'll be quiet.

189
00:09:57,328 --> 00:10:00,728
Excuse me,

190
00:10:00,728 --> 00:10:01,928
but aren't you the famous detective,

191
00:10:01,928 --> 00:10:04,628
Kogoro Mouri?

192
00:10:04,628 --> 00:10:06,328
Uh... yes.

193
00:10:06,328 --> 00:10:09,428
There's something I'd like to discuss with you.

194
00:10:09,428 --> 00:10:10,928
Yes?

195
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,628
We'll start recording now!

196
00:10:30,628 --> 00:10:33,028
Five seconds to air!

197
00:10:33,028 --> 00:10:36,028
Four, three...

198
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:41,128
Welcome to my Cooking Arena!

199
00:10:41,128 --> 00:10:44,828
Please enjoy this sweet evening.

200
00:10:44,828 --> 00:10:47,728
Before announcing tonight's fruit,

201
00:10:47,728 --> 00:10:49,328
I'd like to introduce two guests

202
00:10:49,328 --> 00:10:52,328
we've invited to the arena.

203
00:10:52,328 --> 00:10:55,328
Returning for her second appearance...

204
00:10:55,328 --> 00:10:56,928
Yoko Okino!

205
00:10:56,928 --> 00:10:58,828
Ms. Yoko Okino!

206
00:11:00,728 --> 00:11:03,328
And the other guest is...

207
00:11:03,328 --> 00:11:06,828
the famous detective...

208
00:11:06,828 --> 00:11:09,228
The great Kogoro Mouri!

209
00:11:11,928 --> 00:11:14,528
This turned into a big deal.

210
00:11:14,528 --> 00:11:16,228
He's subbing for Mr. Takegi,

211
00:11:16,228 --> 00:11:19,328
but he doesn't seem nervous at all.

212
00:11:19,328 --> 00:11:21,428
Go get 'em, Dad!

213
00:11:21,428 --> 00:11:22,428
Hmm?

214
00:11:22,428 --> 00:11:23,828
Nah, the ones who need to do their best

215
00:11:23,828 --> 00:11:25,828
are the chefs.

216
00:11:25,828 --> 00:11:29,828
Detective Mouri, do you eat a lot of sweets?

217
00:11:29,828 --> 00:11:33,428
Yes! I have a weakness for sweet things.

218
00:11:33,428 --> 00:11:36,628
Oh, really?

219
00:11:36,628 --> 00:11:39,728
So your wife makes sweets for you often?

220
00:11:39,728 --> 00:11:41,228
My wife?

221
00:11:41,228 --> 00:11:44,628
No way. Her stuff's not even edible.

222
00:11:46,928 --> 00:11:50,428
Mom was really looking forward to this show.

223
00:11:50,428 --> 00:11:52,228
Just don't show it to her.

224
00:11:52,228 --> 00:11:53,828
It's not live anyway.

225
00:11:53,828 --> 00:11:54,828
Hey...

226
00:11:54,828 --> 00:11:58,028
Is it true that Takegi's gone missing?

227
00:11:58,028 --> 00:12:00,828
Yeah. The staff said

228
00:12:00,828 --> 00:12:02,928
they can't get in touch with him at all.

229
00:12:02,928 --> 00:12:04,528
He hasn't come to the studio,

230
00:12:04,528 --> 00:12:07,128
or even to the TV station.

231
00:12:07,128 --> 00:12:10,328
Ah, look, they're opening the box.

232
00:12:10,328 --> 00:12:12,028
Now then,

233
00:12:12,028 --> 00:12:15,428
challenger, Patissier Kuria Enokido,

234
00:12:16,728 --> 00:12:19,928
and champion, Patissier Shuhei Kurimura.

235
00:12:19,928 --> 00:12:21,728
We will announce the fruit

236
00:12:21,728 --> 00:12:24,528
for tonight's battle!

237
00:12:24,528 --> 00:12:27,828
We will use the key

238
00:12:27,828 --> 00:12:29,628
that Producer Taruoka

239
00:12:29,628 --> 00:12:30,728
has kept in the Tohto Bank

240
00:12:30,728 --> 00:12:32,728
safety deposit box as always...

241
00:12:34,528 --> 00:12:39,528
to open this forbidden fruit box!

242
00:12:41,528 --> 00:12:43,128
A padlock like that,

243
00:12:43,128 --> 00:12:44,628
anyone light-fingered

244
00:12:44,628 --> 00:12:47,028
could probably pry it open easily.

245
00:12:47,028 --> 00:12:48,228
But despite how it looks,

246
00:12:48,228 --> 00:12:50,428
it's actually a special lock

247
00:12:50,428 --> 00:12:52,528
with an electronic chip embedded.

248
00:12:52,528 --> 00:12:53,828
If you try to pry it

249
00:12:53,828 --> 00:12:55,828
and stick something in the keyhole,

250
00:12:55,828 --> 00:12:57,528
a buzzer goes off.

251
00:12:57,528 --> 00:13:00,528
I heard you can't easily make a spare key either.

252
00:13:00,528 --> 00:13:02,128
Well, I guess for Kid-sama,

253
00:13:02,128 --> 00:13:04,328
it'd be child's play.

254
00:13:05,728 --> 00:13:09,428
Sera...

255
00:13:09,428 --> 00:13:12,028
I have something to ask you later.

256
00:13:12,028 --> 00:13:15,228
What? Just ask me now.

257
00:13:15,228 --> 00:13:16,828
Okay, then...

258
00:13:18,628 --> 00:13:21,128
Let me show you!

259
00:13:21,128 --> 00:13:23,828
Today's fruit is...

260
00:13:25,928 --> 00:13:28,828
Sera... are you...

261
00:13:28,828 --> 00:13:31,628
like me...

262
00:13:37,428 --> 00:13:38,428
No way.

263
00:13:52,971 --> 00:13:56,671
Isn't that the judge, Mr. Takegi?

264
00:13:56,671 --> 00:13:57,671
No way.

265
00:13:58,971 --> 00:14:01,671
Hey, Conan!

266
00:14:01,671 --> 00:14:03,671
You stay here.

267
00:14:03,671 --> 00:14:04,971
From here on,

268
00:14:04,971 --> 00:14:07,371
it's our territory.

269
00:14:07,371 --> 00:14:09,971
"Us"?

270
00:14:11,771 --> 00:14:14,171
Hey, kid.

271
00:14:17,371 --> 00:14:18,771
No good.

272
00:14:18,771 --> 00:14:20,471
He's already cold.

273
00:14:20,471 --> 00:14:21,871
Looks that way.

274
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:24,771
Cause of death

275
00:14:24,771 --> 00:14:26,671
is probably this wound on the back of his head.

276
00:14:26,671 --> 00:14:28,871
Judging from rigor mortis,

277
00:14:28,871 --> 00:14:31,271
he's been dead for over half a day.

278
00:14:31,271 --> 00:14:32,571
Huh?

279
00:14:32,571 --> 00:14:33,571
On the edge of the box,

280
00:14:33,571 --> 00:14:36,671
there are traces of blood wiped off.

281
00:14:36,671 --> 00:14:38,571
And these marks...

282
00:14:38,571 --> 00:14:40,171
They're on the inside too.

283
00:14:40,171 --> 00:14:42,371
That means...

284
00:14:42,371 --> 00:14:44,371
He hit his head on the box

285
00:14:44,371 --> 00:14:46,571
when the lid was open and died,

286
00:14:46,571 --> 00:14:48,071
and was packed into the box

287
00:14:48,071 --> 00:14:51,071
with the apples.

288
00:14:51,071 --> 00:14:54,171
Is Mr. Takegi really dead?

289
00:14:54,171 --> 00:14:58,371
Yeah. Call the police right away.

290
00:14:58,371 --> 00:15:01,071
And you should have the audience

291
00:15:01,071 --> 00:15:03,671
wait in another room too.

292
00:15:03,671 --> 00:15:06,071
They might have seen something.

293
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:07,371
Then...

294
00:15:07,371 --> 00:15:09,771
let's have Detective Mouri, who's in another room,

295
00:15:09,771 --> 00:15:11,271
come here too.

296
00:15:11,271 --> 00:15:14,871
That'd be better, right, Conan?

297
00:15:14,871 --> 00:15:16,271
You know him?

298
00:15:16,271 --> 00:15:19,371
That's Kenzaki-san. He plays Detective Samonji.

299
00:15:19,371 --> 00:15:21,871
We worked together on a case before.

300
00:15:21,871 --> 00:15:25,571
Oh, that goofy detective.

301
00:15:25,571 --> 00:15:27,371
Goofy?

302
00:15:30,371 --> 00:15:32,071
I see.

303
00:15:32,071 --> 00:15:34,871
So inside this box,

304
00:15:34,871 --> 00:15:37,471
which held the fruit for the cooking competition,

305
00:15:37,471 --> 00:15:39,471
was the body of the head judge,

306
00:15:39,471 --> 00:15:42,471
Mr. Takegi.

307
00:15:42,471 --> 00:15:46,571
We couldn't reach Mr. Takegi for a while,

308
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:49,871
but I never thought he'd be inside the box.

309
00:15:49,871 --> 00:15:51,971
You started the recording

310
00:15:51,971 --> 00:15:54,571
without the head judge?

311
00:15:54,571 --> 00:15:59,471
I happened to be in the audience,

312
00:15:59,471 --> 00:16:02,071
and they chose me as his substitute, Inspector.

313
00:16:02,071 --> 00:16:03,571
Why you?

314
00:16:03,571 --> 00:16:05,571
You're not even a food connoisseur.

315
00:16:05,571 --> 00:16:07,671
I asked the producer to do me a favor.

316
00:16:07,671 --> 00:16:10,071
Since I heard that the recording deadline was approaching,

317
00:16:11,571 --> 00:16:14,771
I thought Mr. Mouri would come forth.

318
00:16:14,771 --> 00:16:17,371
I knew he was going to be at the studio

319
00:16:17,371 --> 00:16:18,871
through the text mail.

320
00:16:18,871 --> 00:16:21,171
Mr. Kenzaki also said that if it were Mr. Mouri,

321
00:16:21,171 --> 00:16:22,271
he would have it easy too,

322
00:16:22,271 --> 00:16:23,571
because he is also an acquaintance.

323
00:16:23,571 --> 00:16:25,071
Isn't that right, Producer Taruoka?

324
00:16:25,071 --> 00:16:27,371
Yeah.

325
00:16:27,371 --> 00:16:28,571
I thought that if it were the great detective Mouri,

326
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:31,371
it would settle in nicely as part of the program, you see.

327
00:16:31,371 --> 00:16:34,271
But, is that rumor about the box keys true?

328
00:16:34,271 --> 00:16:39,071
That they use two locks?

329
00:16:39,071 --> 00:16:41,171
Yes.

330
00:16:41,171 --> 00:16:42,271
First of all,

331
00:16:42,271 --> 00:16:45,771
the food coordinator Mr. Kasuga

332
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:46,771
packs the box with the fruit

333
00:16:46,771 --> 00:16:48,071
that is the theme for the day.

334
00:16:48,071 --> 00:16:49,471
He locks it with a padlock

335
00:16:49,471 --> 00:16:51,171
and sends it to Nichiuri TV.

336
00:16:52,371 --> 00:16:54,471
Then after I receive that box,

337
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:56,171
I lock it with a different padlock

338
00:16:56,171 --> 00:16:58,471
and send it back to Mr. Kasuga's residence.

339
00:16:58,471 --> 00:16:59,971
Then again Mr. Kasuga unlocks the padlock

340
00:16:59,971 --> 00:17:01,071
that he had used at his residence,

341
00:17:01,071 --> 00:17:03,371
and sends it back once again to the TV station.

342
00:17:03,371 --> 00:17:05,971
The MC Kenzaki, at the beginning of the show,

343
00:17:05,971 --> 00:17:07,671
uses the key that he receives from me

344
00:17:07,671 --> 00:17:09,471
to open my padlock.

345
00:17:09,471 --> 00:17:11,071
Here for the first time,

346
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:13,071
everybody finds out what the theme fruit is.

347
00:17:15,371 --> 00:17:18,571
Well, this method is one that Mr. Takegi had proposed

348
00:17:18,571 --> 00:17:19,971
to make sure that the fruit inside the box

349
00:17:19,971 --> 00:17:24,071
would not be leaked beforehand.

350
00:17:24,071 --> 00:17:25,671
Which means...

351
00:17:25,671 --> 00:17:28,571
that the one who could've put the corpse into the box

352
00:17:28,571 --> 00:17:31,171
would be Mr. Kasuga who first locked the box,

353
00:17:31,171 --> 00:17:35,171
or you, who had the last key.

354
00:17:36,071 --> 00:17:37,371
No way...

355
00:17:37,371 --> 00:17:39,771
I do give the key to the MC,

356
00:17:39,771 --> 00:17:41,471
but I do it while the program is being aired, you know?

357
00:17:41,471 --> 00:17:44,071
Until then, the key is stored

358
00:17:44,071 --> 00:17:45,071
in the safety deposit box of Tohto Bank,

359
00:17:45,071 --> 00:17:47,571
and is not in my hands.

360
00:17:47,571 --> 00:17:51,671
The padlock is kept in the drawer of my desk,

361
00:17:51,671 --> 00:17:54,071
and the assistant director (AD) locks the drawer.

362
00:17:54,071 --> 00:17:56,771
Who is that assistant director?

363
00:17:56,771 --> 00:17:58,771
Mr. Furuya right there.

364
00:17:59,871 --> 00:18:02,071
He always locks the drawer

365
00:18:02,071 --> 00:18:04,371
and is also in charge of taking care of the box.

366
00:18:04,371 --> 00:18:06,971
Which means that he's the one who carries it around too?

367
00:18:06,971 --> 00:18:08,471
Although I do take care of the box,

368
00:18:08,471 --> 00:18:11,671
it's not like I watch it 24/7.

369
00:18:11,671 --> 00:18:14,271
Carrying the box around is left to the young assistant directors.

370
00:18:14,271 --> 00:18:16,771
I just accompany them.

371
00:18:16,771 --> 00:18:21,271
Well, there are times that I go alone

372
00:18:21,271 --> 00:18:22,971
to the storage room where the box is kept

373
00:18:22,971 --> 00:18:24,671
to check whether the lock had been pried open or not.

374
00:18:25,671 --> 00:18:26,771
Then if at that time,

375
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:30,371
you sniff the box carefully, wouldn't you be able to tell what's inside the box?

376
00:18:30,371 --> 00:18:31,771
No way!

377
00:18:31,771 --> 00:18:36,571
Because to fill the space between the lid and the box,
a rubber packing like the ones used for refrigerators is attached.

378
00:18:37,871 --> 00:18:42,271
Then the only one left would be Mr. Kasuga,
the first one to lock the box.

379
00:18:42,271 --> 00:18:43,571
Come to think of it,

380
00:18:43,571 --> 00:18:47,871
last night another staff member said that
Mr. Takegi asked for Mr. Kasuga's address.

381
00:18:47,871 --> 00:18:50,771
Then, maybe he went to Mr. Kasuga's home.

382
00:18:50,771 --> 00:18:52,371
Yes.

383
00:18:52,371 --> 00:18:54,071
It's true that Mr. Takegi came over

384
00:18:54,071 --> 00:18:56,471
to my house last night.

385
00:18:56,471 --> 00:18:59,671
Just after I finished packing the box.

386
00:18:59,671 --> 00:19:03,671
Before the staff came to pick up the box.

387
00:19:03,671 --> 00:19:06,671
Mr. Kasuga, what brings you here?

388
00:19:06,671 --> 00:19:09,771
I came because Mr. Takegi called me.

389
00:19:09,771 --> 00:19:14,271
He said that he was going to nab the perp who is leaking information about the contents of the box.

390
00:19:14,271 --> 00:19:17,771
He said that he'd expose the perp while the program is being aired,
so to come and watch.

391
00:19:19,071 --> 00:19:22,771
Then, Mr. Takegi went to your house to...

392
00:19:22,771 --> 00:19:25,871
To check the padlock that I locked

393
00:19:25,871 --> 00:19:27,671
and to make sure that I wasn't doing anything

394
00:19:27,671 --> 00:19:29,871
I wasn't supposed to do.

395
00:19:29,871 --> 00:19:33,271
After all, I'm the only one who knows what's in the box.

396
00:19:33,271 --> 00:19:35,971
He seems to have suspected me

397
00:19:35,971 --> 00:19:37,971
for leaking information about the contents.

398
00:19:39,171 --> 00:19:41,771
And, what did Mr. Takegi do after that?

399
00:19:41,771 --> 00:19:45,271
He left as soon as the staff came

400
00:19:45,271 --> 00:19:46,971
to pick up the box.

401
00:19:46,971 --> 00:19:48,371
Isn't that right?

402
00:19:48,371 --> 00:19:49,571
Yes.

403
00:19:49,571 --> 00:19:51,871
No doubt about it

404
00:19:51,871 --> 00:19:53,471
because two young assistant directors were watching.

405
00:19:53,471 --> 00:19:54,771
Hey...

406
00:19:54,771 --> 00:19:58,771
There's no time to put the corpse in the box then.

407
00:19:58,771 --> 00:20:00,571
Moreover, what bothers me more

408
00:20:00,571 --> 00:20:03,471
is Mr. Takegi's actions.

409
00:20:03,471 --> 00:20:07,671
Why was he going that far to check the box?

410
00:20:07,671 --> 00:20:11,671
Yeah. It sounds like he already knew that

411
00:20:11,671 --> 00:20:14,771
the contents of the box was being leaked outside.

412
00:20:14,771 --> 00:20:17,471
Maybe he just thought it was being leaked

413
00:20:17,471 --> 00:20:19,471
to Mr. Kurimura, the champion,

414
00:20:19,471 --> 00:20:21,571
who won for six consecutive weeks?

415
00:20:21,571 --> 00:20:22,671
Huh?

416
00:20:22,671 --> 00:20:26,171
It seems that he always brought ingredients

417
00:20:26,171 --> 00:20:28,671
that went along well with the theme fruit.

418
00:20:28,671 --> 00:20:30,271
So, maybe he suspected

419
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:32,071
that Kurimura knew the contents of the box.

420
00:20:32,071 --> 00:20:34,571
Is... is that so?

421
00:20:34,571 --> 00:20:35,971
Yes.

422
00:20:35,971 --> 00:20:37,871
At the start Mr. Takegi used to say,

423
00:20:37,871 --> 00:20:40,971
luck was also a talent.

424
00:20:40,971 --> 00:20:42,871
What bothers me even more

425
00:20:42,871 --> 00:20:45,671
is that Mr. Takegi didn't come to this studio,

426
00:20:45,671 --> 00:20:48,071
much less the TV station.

427
00:20:48,071 --> 00:20:50,171
Really?

428
00:20:50,171 --> 00:20:52,171
I know that after the arrangement meeting,

429
00:20:52,171 --> 00:20:55,171
he left the TV station.

430
00:20:56,671 --> 00:20:59,371
If so, where on earth was the corpse

431
00:20:59,371 --> 00:21:00,671
put into the box?

432
00:21:03,871 --> 00:21:05,171
Inspector Megure!

433
00:21:05,171 --> 00:21:06,971
Huh?

434
00:21:06,971 --> 00:21:08,971
It seems that last night Mr. Takegi

435
00:21:08,971 --> 00:21:10,771
secretly came to the TV station

436
00:21:10,771 --> 00:21:13,071
and mingled among the extras of a samurai show.

437
00:21:14,771 --> 00:21:16,171
What?

438
00:21:16,171 --> 00:21:17,971
The director of the samurai show knew Mr. Takegi

439
00:21:17,971 --> 00:21:21,071
who asked him to do a favor.

440
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:22,071
Saying something to the effect that

441
00:21:22,071 --> 00:21:24,371
he wanted to catch his enemy off guard.

442
00:21:24,371 --> 00:21:25,771
I see.

443
00:21:25,771 --> 00:21:26,871
He wanted to make it look

444
00:21:26,871 --> 00:21:28,571
as if he wasn't at the TV station

445
00:21:28,571 --> 00:21:32,071
and wanted to try catching the perp in the act.

446
00:21:32,071 --> 00:21:35,171
Mr. Takegi always wore a kimono,

447
00:21:35,171 --> 00:21:36,471
so it probably would've been easy for him

448
00:21:36,471 --> 00:21:38,371
to mingle among the extras.

449
00:21:38,371 --> 00:21:41,271
If so...

450
00:21:41,271 --> 00:21:43,571
It's very likely that Mr. Takegi was hiding

451
00:21:43,571 --> 00:21:45,571
in the storeroom where the box was stored,

452
00:21:45,571 --> 00:21:48,371
ambushing the perp.

453
00:21:50,571 --> 00:21:52,271
Why?

454
00:21:56,371 --> 00:22:00,871
There were traces of blood being wiped off

455
00:22:00,871 --> 00:22:03,871
by the area where the lid and box match.

456
00:22:03,871 --> 00:22:06,071
That means that the box

457
00:22:06,071 --> 00:22:07,571
was at the scene of the crime, no?

458
00:22:08,871 --> 00:22:10,571
True.

459
00:22:10,571 --> 00:22:12,071
I see.

460
00:22:16,271 --> 00:22:19,671
That's where Mr. Takegi was killed.

461
00:22:22,971 --> 00:22:25,471
By the perp...

462
00:22:29,371 --> 00:22:31,771
Who secretly opened the box.

463
00:22:32,722 --> 00:22:38,734
♪~♪

464
00:23:46,620 --> 00:23:52,382
♪~♪

465
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:55,805
So we've narrowed the suspects down to three.

466
00:23:55,688 --> 00:23:58,394
But who's the culprit?

467
00:23:58,469 --> 00:24:01,650
First off, how they opened the lock is a mystery.

468
00:24:01,434 --> 00:24:02,736
Ah.

469
00:24:03,604 --> 00:24:05,992
I see. So that's it.

470
00:24:06,027 --> 00:24:08,998
Then we should get started soon.

471
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:11,420
Huh? Get started with what?

472
00:24:11,579 --> 00:24:14,217
What? A little...

473
00:24:14,585 --> 00:24:16,472
magic show.

474
00:24:16,897 --> 00:24:18,057
Next Conan...

475
00:24:18,384 --> 00:24:20,000
"A Treasure Box Full of Fruits (Part 2)"

476
00:24:37,754 --> 00:24:40,884
Next Conan's Hint:
"apples"

477
00:24:41,971 --> 00:24:43,098
We're stumped.

478
00:24:43,182 --> 00:24:44,309
Is it because of the apples?

479
00:24:44,392 --> 00:24:46,939
We're up to our apples... I mean, hands.
